name: emp_travel
description: The emp_travel collection maps employee credit card numbers to their travel start dates. Each employee can have multiple travel documents in this collection, which can be retrieved using their credit card number or checked based on travel dates. The document contains fields like travel_start_date (date) and cc_num (credit card number)
usage:
This dataset can be used to fetch which employees are travelling given a time reference, emp_travel will need to be joined using local field cc_num with cc_num field in emp_cc_mapping to figure out the employee identifier. 
This dataset can also be used to figure out how many employees have travelled so far

name: emp_transactions
description: emp_transactions contain transactions done by an employee using a credit card. This also captures informations such as trans_date_trans_time(time when transaction was done), cc_num(credit card number), merchant(name of the merchant), category(category of the transaction), amt(amount of the transaction), first(first name of the employee), last(last name of the employee),gender(gender of employee), street(street address of the employee), city(city of the employee), state(state of the employee), zip(zip code of the employee), lat(latitude of the employee), long(longitude of the employee), city_pop(population of the city), job(job of the employee), dob(date of birth of the employee),trans_num(transaction identifier), unix_time(unix time of the transaction), merch_lat(latitude of the merchant), merch_long(longitude of the merchant) and is_fraud(whether the transaction is fraud or not)
usage: This dataset can be joined using local field  cc_num and trans_date_trans_time with emp_travel on cc_num and travel_start_date to figure out if an employee used a credit card when not on travel and performed fraud

name: emp_attendance
description: emp_attendance stores official attendance information of employees on a daily basis. It has fields emp_id (employee identifier), date (date when attendance was locked) and attendance (has values present , on official duty, absent)
usage: This dataset can be used to identify if an employee was present in office or was on official duty or was absent on a given day.

name: emp_cc_mapping
description: emp_cc_mapping maps which employee is using which credit card. It has fields empi_id(employee identifier) and cc_num (credit card number) only. This does not have any employee specific information.
usage: This dataset can be used to get employee details using credit card numbers by joining based on cc_num to other employee related tables
